# Python Port Plan ‚Äî Step 01: Struct Skeleton

## Goal

Port `week1_baseline/ruby/01_struct_skeleton` to
`week1_baseline/python/01_struct_skeleton`. This step adds three new data
types on top of step 0's `Config`/`Tasks::Base`/`Tasks::Player`: `Tool` and
`Message` (Ruby `Struct`s) and `Context` (a plain class that holds
everything needed for one agent run ‚Äî task, system prompt, messages,
registered tools). Same behavior, same example output shape, same shared
`.boukensha/` fixture directory as the Ruby version.

